message: While the Bud Light delivery guys may seem unlikely crime fighters, Porter and an industry official explained that because of their regular access to thousands of businesses in the state, they're in a good position to notice something off-kilter.

data.description: The Texas Alcoholic Beverage Commission wants alcohol delivery people to be on the lookout for signs of human trafficking in TABC-licensed bars,...
data.title: TABC taps alcohol distributors to help fight human trafficking at bars, restaurants, liquor stores
